			    STPJS 367</div>
  <p class="cont">me shall see it, and know that I testify the truth concerning them.</p>
  <div class="topic">The Resurrection Universal</div>
  <p class="std">In regard to the law of the Priesthood,<span class="footRef">1</span> there should be a place where all nations shall come up<span class="footRef">2</span>
  from time to time to receive their endowments;<span class="footRef">3</span> and the Lord has said this shall be the place for the
  baptisms for the dead.<span class="footRef">4</span> Every man that has been baptized and belongs to the kingdom has a right to
  be baptized for those who have gone before; and as soon as the law of the Gospel<span class="footRef">5</span> is obeyed here
  by their friends who act as proxy for them, the Lord has administrators there to set them free.<span class="footRef">6</span> A man
  may act as proxy for his own relatives; the ordinances of the Gospel which were laid out before the
  foundations of the world<span class="footRef">7</span> have thus been fulfilled by them, and we may be baptized for those whom
  we have much friendship for; but it must first be revealed to the man of God,<span class="footRef">8</span> lest we should run too
  far.<span class="footRef">9</span> &ldquo;As in Adam all die, even so in Christ shall all be made alive;&rdquo;<span class="footRef">10</span> all shall be raised from the
  dead.<span class="footRef">11</span> The Lamb of God hath brought to pass the resurrection,<span class="footRef">12</span> so that all shall rise from the
  dead.<span class="footRef">13</span></p>
  <p class="std">God Almighty Himself dwells in eternal fire;<span class="footRef">14</span> flesh and blood cannot go there,<span class="footRef">15</span> for all
  corruption is devoured by the fire. &ldquo;Our God is a consuming fire.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">16</span> When our flesh is quickened
  by the Spirit,<span class="footRef">17</span> there will be no blood in this tabernacle. Some dwell in higher glory than others.<span class="footRef">18</span></p>
  <p class="std">Those who have done wrong always have that wrong gnawing them.<span class="footRef">19</span> Immortality dwells in
  everlasting burnings.<span class="footRef">20</span> I will from time to time reveal to you the subjects that are revealed by the
  Holy Ghost to me.<span class="footRef">21</span> All the lies<span class="footRef">22</span> that are now hatched up<span class="footRef">23</span> against me are of the devil,<span class="footRef">24</span> and the
  influence of the devil and his servants will be used against the kingdom of God.<span class="footRef">25</span> The servants of
  God<span class="footRef">26</span> teach nothing but principles of eternal life, by their works ye shall know them.<span class="footRef">27</span> A good man
  will speak good things and holy principles, and an evil man evil things.<span class="footRef">28</span> I feel, in the name of the
  Lord, to rebuke all such bad principles, liars,<span class="footRef">29</span> &amp;c., and I warn all of you to look out whom you are
  going after. I exhort you to give heed to all the virtue and the teachings<span class="footRef">30</span> which I have given you.
  All men who are immortal dwell in everlasting burnings.<span class="footRef">31</span> You cannot go anywhere but where God
  can find you out.<span class="footRef">32</span> All men are</p>
